Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water
with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil for the potato chunks.

From your @potatoes{450}, slice some 1cm thick rounds, 3 per person (no need to peel)
- these are going to be your 'gravestones'. Chop the remaining potatoes into 2cm chunks.

Lay the gravestones onto a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until softened, ~{18-20%minutes}. 
Turn halfway through.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the potato chunks and cook until you can easily
slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces. Trim the
@green beans{150}. Peel and grate the @garlic{3%cloves}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a #frying pan{} with a drizzle of @oil{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and onion. Fry until browned,
~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard
any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Add half the garlic and @dried rosemary{1} to the beef. Cook, stirring, for ~{30%secs}.

Stir in the @red wine jus paste{15}, @onion marmalade{20} and @water{100%ml}(for the sauce).
Bring the mixture to the boil, then reduce the heat slightly and simmer until thickened,
~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the
pot, off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @?milk{splash} and mash with a
#potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once the potato gravestones have softened, remove them from the oven.

Once thickened, transfer the beef filling into an #ovenproof dish{} and top with an
even layer of mashed potato.

Stick the gravestones into the mashed potatoes to make your 'graveyard'. Scatter the
@grated hard Italian style cheese{25} over the top.

Pop the ovenproof dish onto the (now empty) baking tray and bake on the top shelf
of your oven until golden, ~{7-8%minutes}.

Wipe out the (now empty) #mince frying pan{} and pop on medium-high heat with a
drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the remaining garlic, then turn the heat down to medium and cook for
~{1%minute}.

Add a splash of @water{} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. Cook
until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

When ready, share your graveyard beef and onion pie between your plates.

Serve the green beans alongside.

Enjoy!